\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Name? Better have the full name. Mary Emily Rosser.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Belmont{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}11 Westfield Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Whitchurch, Cardiff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And your marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Single.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh. Well that's a dead secret supposed to be. May the seventeenth 1890. And don't tell - don't tell -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 I was born - in a house by the name of Prospect House, on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Wood Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in Pontypridd. Glamorgan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh - about - five years or - five or six years. And then we moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 We moved - to Gelliwastad Grove, Pontypridd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh - about - '95 we left Prospect House - 'til after I'd been to college. After -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You were five then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 In 1895 you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When did you go to college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 About -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was it during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 I wasn't sure - it - I went in - the year war started. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You were there three years were you, four years you were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Cardiff
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Yes. Well I - took a course in - special infant work first of all, and a National - Froebel course. And then - I - taught for - for some years. And then I went back and took a Government certificate. I took a year in - secondary training.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you move then after you did that or when you first came out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I moved - after the war - after the - oh I aren't I awful for dates. When did we came down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You moved from Gelliwastad to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Cardiff{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You were only in the two houses in Pontypridd were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you remember why you moved from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Prospect Place{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} to Gelliwastad Grove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well my father - was - a - a lawyer in the town of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Pontypridd{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And - my mother used to feel - that he was too long all day, without
 - of course - it wasn't prevalent as it is today to go out to meals. And on court days when he had to go to the court, he'd be - she said he was too long, it would be better - for us to be living - nearer his place of work. So - he could come home and ha
ve a snack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When did you move down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Cardiff{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 About - 1918 I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you remember why you moved then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh because the rates went up too much at Pontypridd and - we felt that - the - this - was an area for - then - where - they
 used to give a grant towards - the Government gave a - what - what - oh what do they call it - a - a - an area - where - what shall I say, the people - there was unemployment and there was so much - the rates wentup so much and it - we felt that - Pontyp
ridd were not giving us anything for our rates. And - oh well, what's the word I want? For -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your father still continued in Pontypridd did he when you were living down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 OH my father never came down here. He died when he was fifty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 One sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you remember her birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 January the twel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 th - two years younger than I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When would she be born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 1888 was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 That's older than you, was she younger or older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, older than I. Oh did I say younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How old was your father when you were born? He would have been thirty-eight when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Aberdare. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Cwm{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Aberdare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 A lawyer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did he have another job before he became a lawyer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did he ever do any other work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no, not - only just - a lawyer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 She came from - Abergavenny. Out of - Hard, just outside Abergavenny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she have any job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. She was the headmistress of the Garig school - in Pontypridd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was it a junior school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 It was - there were only two kinds of schools, infants - and - standard like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Up to fourteen year olds was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well they left at fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 The children who didn't go to the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well there wasn't a grammar school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 It was an all age school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And she was a headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 I think she worked - for a few years, but not - not so many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she continue in the same job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. I think they wanted to buy their house you see, and she - worked in order to get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she have any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. Oh except - except - that she was interested in education and she was a co-opted member - for the Education Authorit
y - on the Education Authority for the Pontypridd council - in those days they had to have - one woman. And she was chosen you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 I'd like to ask you about life at home when you were a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Up to the time when you left school, so I think the Gwlliwastad house is the one to talk about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Well I didn't go to school much - until - I went to Gelliwastad Road, because in those days they didn't have play groups did they.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How many rooms were there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where,
 in - oh - there were four on the first floor. Three - bedrooms on the second, that's seven. You don't want to know - the bathroom and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Could you describe the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well - there were four rooms - I'll begin at the cellar then. The cellar - 
there was a cellar at the bottom - with about - ten or twelve steps, step stone steps to go down, to the cellar. And - it - went off the hall. Then there were - three - there was the dining room and lounge and kitchen and scullery. And two pantries, one w
e
 called - the food pantry, the other the china pantry. And then we went upstairs and there were - three bedrooms there, and I think - there had been four, but the - bath room - had been a bedroom converted I think. And then - the - toilet was in the same 
room as the bathroom. And then there was another floor, there were four bedrooms on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did anyone else besides your parents and your sister live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well, that - that cousin that was brought up my mother adopted lived there too. And we had a grown up maid living in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So this cousin was your brother really, perhaps you could tell me about that, your; adopted brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 He was - my mother's sister's son. And his father was a schoolmaster, and his mother and father died within
 six months of each other. And really - he was supposed to have stayed in Abergavenny with my grandmother - to go to school. But then of course - the weather was very bad and there were no buses - in the - there was not as much - car business as there is 
t
oday. And - so my mother - went over to her home to the farm for a holiday, and she brought him back with her. In order for him to come to school because - he could come to school - it was nearer in Pontypridd for him to come - from her rooms, she was in 
rooms then, she wasn't married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 This was before she was married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Yes. And she had him - there. And then when my mother and father were going to get married - he was supposed to be going back. And my father said, oh no, I think we'd better keep him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How old would he have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I expect he was only about - seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So they kept him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And they kept him. So - there was my father and mother - Ori as we called him - and my sister and I and this big maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And the maid lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Just one servant you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. And we used to have a woman to come in to - to do the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So you had one all round maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. General.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What did you call her really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well we had a few of t
hem. Only different times. And one we used to call Mildred. Because - my mother's name was Annie and this girl's name was Annie. So we had to - she didn't have another name so we used to call her Morgan. And she was from Cardigan. And she used to go to Pe
rivale Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What would her work be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh general housework I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where would she sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 She slept on the fourth floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where would she eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was there a room or anywhere where she could sit while she was not working?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Well no, we were small and I think she used to come to us a lot, because - my mother and father always had a - a meal - their meal - in the - breakfast room, and then they retired to the dining room always. And left the breakfast
 room for us - to do our homework and play. And she used to sit with us a lot, partly - I expect - so the - came - they - they felt they could go out if they wanted to, and she - went out twice a week. On a Wednesday night - and on a Sunday. Wouldn't do t
hat today would they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Sunday night was it, not Sunday all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh dear no. Sunday - Sunday - after tea. And she came in by ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your mother supervise all the housework personally or did she leave it to Morgan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - she wa
s - I don't know whether - she became delicate but she had a bit of kidney trouble. And she wasn't very well so she had to leave a lot - to her that she wouldn't otherwise have left. And she was a serious sort of girl - that - you know, she used to leave 
the care of us very often to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 To Morgan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You had a woman as well who came in to wash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh, she was - a Mrs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101  Perriman, and she lived - not far from the old bridge at Pontypridd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she come in one day a week, or what exactly would she have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - one day a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What exactly would she have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh the general washing. You know, the sheets and the - and the - the general }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 changing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101  as they used to call it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she do the ironing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Who would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Morgan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would Morgan supervise the washerwoman or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 My mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you feel at ease with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How did they address each other, Morgan and the washerwoman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh - just - she used - she used to call her Morgan and Mrs Perriman used to - be addressed as Mrs Perriman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How would you address them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you feel then that they were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Because - I - I say m
y mother wasn't very strong, but - Morganwould come to us on a Sunday morning - or - and other mornings, and she would - say, if you be good girls you can - come to the kitchen, it was a great treat, and have your breakfast there. Because - normally - we 
had our breakfast served in the breakfast room. But - she more or less took charge of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When you say the breakfast room, downstairs you had the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. And a scullery behind it. And then we had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 veranda}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 . And then it - let into the hall, and then - to the right there was the breakfast room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then did you have a dining room and a lounge separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Separate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You had two rooms as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Two big rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your mother give any moral guidance to the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
I don't think there was any need to. I don't think there was any need to at all. They used to - talk a bit in Welsh to one another, and - I think the - they were all brought up in the same atmosphere. She'd come from a - a God fearing hom
e - to us. So I don't think there was - any need for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Were they allowed any time to do just what they liked? It would be Morgan really not the washerwoman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, she'd be gone.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When you had living in servants would they be allowed any time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh yes. I think - after they - served the evening - meal - it was generally sort of tea about six o'clock when they finished - my father came from the office. And then her - her time was hers then 'til - it was supper
time. Then she served the supper and then she could go to bed or do what she liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 But only twice a week she would go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Wednesday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And Sunday. But of course of later days - we used to - when - after my mother and fath
er had passed on, we - used to allow the maid out every night. Times changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your mother mind what they did then when they went out? Or what time they returned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well she - liked them in by ten o'clock. But I don't think she interfered with their - private life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your father help your mother at all with any jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Good heavens, no. I don't think he knew the business side of a hammer. And of course - labour was very cheap in those days. And if a - screw came out of
 the door he wouldn't know how to put it back. But he'd say, send for a man. And we used to have a man, we called him Sion Cadwgan, and he came to the same chapel as we did, and he was a painter and general handy man. So - anything went wrong - with the h
ose we sent for Sion Cadwgan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would he ever dress or undress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, I don't remember my father ever doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 I don't think he was in a lot to read to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No I don't think I - we had a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh yes. Very often. I'll tell you where he used to take us. On - on Easter Monday to a fair. There used to be - a - a fair - came to Pontypridd. Yes. Easter Mo
nday was - a very quiet day otherwise, but - the fair used to be held - in - now where the Y.M.C.A. in Pontypridd is now, there was a field opposite, I don't know whether it's built on now, or - but it was running down to the river. And the fair was held 
t
here. And of course - it - we were round eyed with - you know - looking at - the fair, and the tinsels you know, all - that you could see is gold, not - not that old - you don't see is gold. And he was very generous with us - to take us out and anything n
e
w come into Pontypridd. Like - when the first trams came to Pontypridd. Took us down to see - the opening of that. And then he took us down to this fair - and put us on - the horses, and the roundabouts and took us to buy home made toffee. And then took u
s
 to see - a big fat woman or the big fat man, whatever it was. And he used to give us - Easter Monday morning a round to taking us. And very often we took the people - my father would take the people from next door. They were the Hopkin Morgan's. The - yo
u know, the - confectioners, bakers. And - we were great friends, they were Pennywell people and we were St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
s people, but - if there was anything on - either Mr Morgan or Mr Rosser took one or the other lot. Took the two lots of children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your mother wouldn't go with you on Easter Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
No. I - I don't think she was well enough - to stand the rough and tumble. And the pushing about. And we - he'd always - you know - have a bit of fun with the coconuts and that sort of thing. There was - pl
enty of go in him. But I don't remember him telling us stories much - but he'd - always be ready to take us to anything new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would he look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. But as I say - in those days - office hours were not office hours in the sense they are today. At - five o'clock ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
thing's closed up isn't it? Well - that not - that was not so then. And - the miners used to - the ones that were - good type - would like to buy their houses, and they'd come down then - to see my fa
ther after work, they'd be doing overtime perhaps. Then they'd come perhaps about - half past seven or eight o'clock. And my father'd always see them. And he'd do business then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would it be in the house or in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 It would be in the house
. But he'd always - do - do business with them, he'd always see them. Because he knew they couldn't come - any other time. And they worked - as adamant about - hours as they are today. And I think that's part of the downfall of this country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. No, we just - got up, had our breakfast and - when it was holiday time went out to play, that was the end.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You didn't have any little job you had to do at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
No. We - shopping we'd have to do for my mother. Yes. But that's all. She'd say, run and get apples or - go down to the grocers for me. But - there was no little job in the house like - cleaning the knives or - no. Well we had a maid that did everything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What about after you left school, did you have to do any jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh yes, but I think it was because - we had - beginning to have ideas then. And we wanted to - put them into practice more than - we were bound to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would your sister have any jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
No. But - she was very fond of needlework. And she went in for - domestic arts. But - and I'll tell you what my mother used to want us to do a lot, she was interested in various things, collecting - for the nurses. Th
e nurse - there was a - now of course - it's all paid for in the health, but they used to be - a nurses - home - where there were two or three nurses living together. And they were - kept by public subscription. And my mother was on the committee, and of 
course - she'd - have a quota to - try and go round districts and - she used to - very often - get me to go round - to - for the subscriptions. To save her walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What about your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 She - well - she wasn't so keen on doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 She wouldn't do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Well she - we were as different as chalk and cheese. And that - man I asked you about if you knew, Mr Milton Jones - he used to call us - Mr and Mrs Rosser because I was so like my father and she was so like my mother. And - she used to 
- I don't know whether I was softer - or - or what it was but - she used to get me to do those jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Because she was older than you did your sister help you to do things you found difficult to do when you were little, like dressing or eating? Did she have to look after you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. I don't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you help her in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh - no. No. Not until she was ill, you know, or - of course if one or the - the other of us wasn't well we'd do what we could. But - we didn't have to - we were sort of self - maintaining.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes, I should say. We had to go to bed about - I think about eight o'clock in the winter, and I think it was about nine o'clock in t
he summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. We used to go ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And - we'd be frightened of the dark, and then she'd - sometimes lie on the bed with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Morgan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she take you to bed, not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
No, she as a rule. Because my mother - was delicate and she didn't go up the stairs more than she could help. She took great care of herself. And funnily enough when she died the doctor said tha
t had she not taken such - care of herself she wouldn't have lived so long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So Morgan would put you to bed when you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So you shared the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And bed with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What were the sleeping arrangements for the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
My mother and father had a double bed - and of course slept together. And the maid of course had - her own room upstairs. And - my cousin - had his - bedroom. On the fourth floor. Yes. Not because - it w
as because there was no more room you see. All the bedrooms were used.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would Morgan sleep on the same floor as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. Not unless - one of us weren't well or something like that. And - she'd - sometimes say, I'll sleep with you tonight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You had two main bedrooms on the first floor because one bedroom had been used for a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, we'd three main bedrooms. And there was one - bedroom we always called the preacher's room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You kept one room empty as a guest room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. But it was mainly the preacher - the preacher - the preacher's room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So your father and mother were in the main bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then you and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then there was another one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 A spare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then Morgan and your cousin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Up at the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would your cousin have had any jobs to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
No. Because - I don't think he was very - keen on doing jobs. He was not very handy, not - I think the men of today are more handy than they had - than they used to be. Because - labour's so dear now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - we were - there used to be a - a - have a wash down every down. And a bath - you know, get in the bath and wallow in it for - as lo
ng as you like - once a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh once a week, unless an accident happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 In the breakfast room mostly, unless we had visitors. Then it was - the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So there were occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What occasions would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - when we had - a visitor to tea, or we had the minister for weekends. Then of course - we - he'd have all his meals in the dini
ng room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you all have your meals there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well generally we were given our meal before he came down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 The children would still have it in the breakfast room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Or in the kitchen with Morgan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 The kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What was the cooking equipment, a range or gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Gas. Yes. And we had one of those - old fashioned boilers. Which we boiled the - Christmas puddings. She'd make about - a dozen Christmas puddings, and then she'd - boil them in
 this boiler where the clothes used to be boiled in. It used to be a regular - day out - washing day. Had to - put a fire underneath this old boiler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your mother would make the Christmas puddings would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 My mother made the puddings, yes. And 
she always made the cake. You know - any - sort of cooking like that. But as a rule - Morgan did the ordinary dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well I think it depended on school days. And when my father wanted to - go out. I think it was - roug
hly between eight and - eight - and nine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What members of the family were present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 My father, my mother - and - my cousin and - we two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So you'd all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, except Morgan, she'd have hers - in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she have it af}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 er or be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 ore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh I think it depended - on how - things went. If there were - we all came down together she'd - come and - serve us and then sit down and have hers. And other - other times she'd want to - have her meal - she'd just take it before anybody came down.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What did you usually eat or drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Well we - we used to have - very often my mother used to - give us - senna tea. Do you - do you know - senna tea before breakfast - because she thought it was good for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you have it every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh no. Only - sort of once a week or something like that. Then we'd have tea. And then we'd have bacon - and egg. And toast and marmalade. But we didn't have cereals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you have anything different on certain days, like Saturday or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Yes, on Sunday - it was always plainer. We didn't have a cooked breakfast on a Sunday morning, because - we had to get ready to go to church. Church figured on our horizon on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What about midday meals, when would you have the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 About one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Who would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 My mother - and - my cousin and Gladys and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Not your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Very often - he - he worked - if he could he would be there but it wasn't a
 rule, because sometimes he was at court you see and he couldn't get there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What did you usually have to eat and drink for the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would it be your main meal, your dinner, or was it just lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, it would be - dinner.
 It depended. Sometimes - on Monday it would be - cold or from Sunday. On Tuesday or Wednesday perhaps it would be liver. And - Wednesday - Wednesday and Thursday - it would be - some kinds of - of meat, but generally Friday we had fish. And Saturday we g
enerally had sausages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And - oh well Sunday we had the - usual cooked dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What was the next meal, would there be an evening meal or would you have tea or a high tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh we had tea. Tea and cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 We came - when we came back from Sunday school on a Sunday. But at other times we'd have it about - half past four to five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 In the weekdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What members of the family would be present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well - it - sometimes my mother. And sometimes it would be only my sister and myself
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What would you have to eat and drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh well we'd have - depended upon the weather. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 
Sometimes we'd - have - pickle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 s. Cooked and - other times - Shrove Tuesdays and that sort of thing you know we'd have pancakes. And then we'd have - Welsh cakes as a rule. And tart always.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh tea always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you have anything different on certain days, you mentioned Shrove Tuesday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And Sunday or Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Well Saturday - it was - it became a little - as we grow - grew older - that we used to go down to Cardiff Saturday afternoon, and have our meal in Cardiff in the Dutch - or in the Dorothy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you have an evening meal again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, we had a supper. But it was a very plain supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
That would be about - half past eight to nine. And very often - it would be - in the summer lemonade. But in the winter it would be a cup of tea. And then - we - sometimes it would be toasted cheese or - you know - whatever we fancied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Who would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - my sister and I generally, but - my mother and father sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would they have had a meal earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. Because -
 my father came home from the office about six. And there was always a meal for him then. And he had that more or less - my mother and father had that alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Not regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Not regularly, no. Because we didn't have a proper baking oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 She wouldn't do a lot of bottling - 'cos - they were cheaper then weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Wine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. Only I do wines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh dear - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would they have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Not much, they didn't - weren't believers in tinned stuff. Mind you - the market was near you see, and - we - when we lived at the - at the Grove she could easily slip down the market, for cabbage or a cauliflower or - beans or peas whatever they were.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your family keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. Dog and a cat always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well I think we all took an interest in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How many times did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 l I m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
yself wasn't a - very great meat eater. And I remember the doctor, Doctor - Jenkins - then - my mother saying - that I ate a lot of cheese. I was very fond of cheese. And - she - wondered - if it was good for me
 but - he said, well does she take much meat? And - my mother said, no, she's not very fond of meat. Well you ought to thank - thank God that she's got a digestion to - digest the cheese, because - that's just as good for her as the meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 But there was meat provided was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes, yes. It was just I personally - so - well, I preferred the cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How many times would meat be on the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh - I think it would be - on the table - most times because - sometimes you see my father - 
could have - had been a long time without a meal and well the meat was put for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Tongue we used to have. But I don't remember anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would that be tinned tongue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Or would it be tongue you did yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh my mother used to do the tongue herself. But - we did buy tinned tongue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You never had tinned corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, we never bought that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. But 
I think we used to have it, but probably they were given as gifts. We used to get a tremendous lot of gifts. My father I think, did - did a lot of work for people, and I don't think he charged them - or charged them as much - as he should have. 'Cos there
 wasn't - a set - fee like they've got now. The Law Society have a set fee haven't they. But they didn't have that then you see. And - Christmastime - my mother was a farmer's daughter, and of course, their - she'd put the best side to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and she'd - s
he was very - keen on - on saving too. So that really she - at Christmastime very often - we'd have - so much poultry that we wouldn't know what to do with it. So she used to take it down to the butchers - and the butcher used to keep count of what she br
ought - and then - later in the year giver her back in - in meat - what - she got in poultry - from her father's trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You'd have the poultry given you at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. Very often - I can remember - as much as five or six turkeys in the pant
ry at the same time, well you couldn't - possibly - do with them. So you had to do something didn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 It would be from customers really you'd have the extra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Yes - people - yes, people - that wanted - knowledge and favours I expect. They don't come now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 It would be at Christmastime mainly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Not at other times of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no, Christmastime mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh dear no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. Well he'd - he had what he wanted. But he didn't have it because - it was short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh we were brought up to - learn to eat what was put on our plates. Because it was good for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well if they knew we were w
ell - and it was a bit of nonsense, we'd have to eat it. But if they - thought - that we really couldn't eat it, it was genuine, well we were allowed to let - go out. Or the dog had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101  did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I think we - used to pass the salt round at the beginning of a meal always. And the pepper. Vinegar whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Supposing you wanted it in the middle of the meal, would you be able to ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I think we were taught - how to - use our - utensils prop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 
erly, and to sit properly and acc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 ur}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 ely on our seat. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When we were told. Generally after we'd eaten our m
eal we - we were - say, well you children go out to play if you want to. Because my mother and father - never - discussed or spoke about anybody - in the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101  church or the town in our pres}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 ence. They were never discussed in our hearing. Whatever they had to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How was the meal served, by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well the table was laid - and then - the meal was brought in, and then - my fathe
r - carved - and my mother - gave out the vegetables. And the pudding the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So really the vegetables would be brought in on tureens would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And put on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 By - by the maid. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And the meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then your mother would serve you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 In what order would you be served then? Your father would carve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And he would put the meat out on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How would the food be given out, to whom first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I - I think - he cut for my mother first and then - go around in order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How did you sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 V used to sit - to my mother's right. And my cousin - and Gladys used to sit opposite her. Then my father, he used to - sit to her left.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would it be a round table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no. A square table. Good size square dining table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your father would be at one end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then your mother next to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 me around the corner. Then \endash  Ori}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8088101  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 would be - next to me, then my sister - yes, then she was - there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You were the youngest in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So you wouldn't remember where you sat before you could feed yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 The servants never ate at all with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did they have different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Never. Always the same. Same food. Although they didn't a lot in those days have the same food. Mrs Craddock, up - there - she never - she always locked up her food. I've been 
there - and she'd say of course - can't make cakes for servants and all, and she'd put the cakes out first, and then - lock them up in the sideboard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What did they have I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well they could make - they could make their own cakes. But of cou
rse - in those days - very often you could get poorer food couldn't you. I don't know what they'd do - she'd be tarred, feathered and what you call it today wouldn't she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 But the servants always had the same meals in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes, the same food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, I think she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. She was very affectionate. And she was very proud. But she was very religious too. That's my mother. Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would she sort of kiss you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. She always - we - when we went out or when we came in we always kissed one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your father and your mother or just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 My father too, yes, my father was - he gave us all one before he went in the
 morning. Yes. Yes. And if he'd been out a long day he'd always come in and give you a kiss first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you kiss them before you went to bed at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh always. Always went up, said goodnight and give him a kiss. But there was one thing that -
 we always had to show my father - respect, my mother - would - say - we come in in the evening, perhaps a bit tired, and he - she - she'd say to you, your father's been out working all day. You get out of that chair now - there are plenty of other chairs
 for you to go to, perhaps you would be sitting in his special chair. He'd a special armchair and my mother a special chair. And those - were all right to sit in if they were not there, but if they were there we had to - leave them blank for them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, yes, I would. I think that's what you miss most when your mother dies. Sharing your worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Very easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And he showed you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. I could get round my father, I couldn't get round mother always. If I wanted something very much it was my father I'd go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How would you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 And I'd say, you know, I want so and so and so and so. Well we'll see 
