Oh dear, no. That's a myth. Don't you think so? Well - this is how I looked upon it. I've got - not a lot of money but I've got some money in the Building Soci
ety. They pay - they - throw dust in my eyes, that they're paying - my - income tax on it. But the same people are lending out - far higher than ever offered me or near it. There's a big space between - what they pay me for the loan and what they - and - 
a
nd what they lent it out. Well of course they've got these big places to keep going. And they've got these big services - big - big - offices to maintain. So I'm sure that they - it - it's - a profit making concern and they're glad to have - silly little 
things like me to lend them a bit now and again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 If you had any worries would you share them with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
