would meet us. Sometimes Morgan would meet us. But we were never - and he never - allowed us to - travel - in compartments on the railway alone. Because - in those days there used to be a train going - from Pontypridd to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cardiff{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and it didn't stop at Refor
est always, and there was a long run to Carswell and there were no communication cords. And he would not allow us to travel in that train alone. Somebody was sent to take us - to - and I think a lot of - the - people who go wrong today, it's because they 
don't get - the sort of - care that they should get. And of course we were never allowed to go to a dance un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1858084\charrsid8088101 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
