life mauve. And was all colours of the rainbow by now. And - she was digging in - some grain or something in - in the - yard, so she came in and she said, excuse me, are you the new governess? So I said, yes, I'm afraid I am. So she said - well I hope I w
i
ll suit you, she said. Well I thought, it's only - you suited me but I've got to suit you as well and everybody else. Well - my brother - was - up at DenRoyal in Caerphilly, and he had been head - up there. And - if there's any difficulty you're in, he'd 
come up and give you a helping hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 This woman said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
This woman said. And her name was Maggie. And then we had - some very interesting gypsies living near. And they - I never made out quite whether they were dull - or whether - they were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280004\charrsid8088101 c}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 raft
y, or whether they told lies. Because I had to take a class as I told you, and a knock came at the door one day. And somebody said, oh Miss, Gipsy Lee's there. Oh I thought, well that's a - that's a new acquaintance. I heard of Gipsy Lee. So I said, well 
s
he'd better come in, 'cos I couldn't go to the door and let the children play behind me could I. So - she came in, this woman with a black hat with a feather, you know these ostrich feathers that was - and she said, I hear that you're the first lady of Na
n
gowell. Which - sort of - pandered to my self-importance, but not much. And - she'd had an income tax form. And she couldn't make head or tail of it, or said she couldn't. So I didn't know what to do with it. So I said, well - they want to know where you 
w
ere born. Could you tell me where you were born? I don't know, outside some big town. Which wasn't very helpful. Well - well - there's a big common outside Swansea. Do you think you were born in Swansea? You weren't born round here? No, it was - away from
 
here. So - anyhow - I wrote down - what I - could filch from her - scatterbrain, and I said, I think the best thing is - for you to go up to the office - and let them see you, and then if you don't understand - they said, I don't understand what they tell
 
me, well tell them to write it down on a bit of paper, and bring the paper back to me and I'll try and - work it out for you. So - so off she went. And the next - I telephoned - and asked if they could see her the next day. So - she went up there - to see
 them. And they sent back - that they couldn't make head or tail of her, and they wondered how I'd ever got the information I had got, out of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you have any other job after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, I retired from there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Yes. I would rather have gone in for law. Yes. But I was a bit - too young, or too old. Because - we were only allowed to practice law in America at that time. But I thought that being as my father -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You have liked to have been a lawyer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Yes. I think I would have. But I don't know whether I would have liked - the hard - dry reading. But I'd have liked the position and I would have liked - I don't know, I think I was always a bit argumentative, and I think I - I - wo
uld rather have excelled - in County Court work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 There was no question of you going in for it was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well no because - I - I could have been articled but then you see I couldn't have practiced in this country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 There were no women then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs, you did because you went for two and a half years and then another year didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So you had three and a half years really training?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you belong to a trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes, the National Union of Teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, I - on strike - because - well everybody - Poole was the man then, do you remember Poole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 He was the Member of Parliament for Port Talbot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Yes. Well - he was the Secretary of the N.U.T., and I remember going to him and I thought well I'm not quite as - I'm - engaged as a Froebel teacher. That was before I went back you see, the seco
nd time. And - I wondered if I - ought to go on strike or whether I'd find myself out of a job. And he said, oh no, you do what the others do, you come with us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you have any particular job in the trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You were an active member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you go to the meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh yes. But in a way - Pontypridd became very - political. The Labour people rather took over. And I think a lot of people - stayed away that ought to have come. Because you miss - the professional side don't you, by not going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You mean at the N.U.T. meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You felt the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Had rather taken over. Yes. Well - and that was the cause of - because a lot of people then belonged to the union but they never go t
o meetings. And Chick, do - do you know Chick, he was a - a big Labour man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did it keep you away from the meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no, it didn't keep me - but I went - but I wasn't an active member, I paid my subscription, and I think I did it more - for - 
safety of my job more than - more than that I - was keen on the principle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you feel that the employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh mainly about the same interests. Because it was the opening out then of - of the working man - coming into his own more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. Well - that's individuality in a way isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh there was, yes. Yes. Yes. Because the trained craftsmen - were not paid - as much in proportion as they should have been. Because the other man - came and pushed in but they didn't take - the same interest in the job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You felt that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. Because - it isn't only now - this dearth of workers. This has been coming on for years hasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What about up to the end of the first world war, what did you think about it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, oh well - we used to go to - First Aid classes and home nursing and St. John's Ambulance, we used to do all those sort of things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. And I think it's good for everybody - to have a full time
 job, but - I think - now - the married woman has overstepped herself. I'm not against - a married woman because she is married in a job. But I'm against her - going to a job and not pulling her weight when she's there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 There were married women in school then weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Oh yes. Yes, they were beginning. And - my sister in the grammar school, they used to have a - a lot of extraneous duties. And a lot of the married women would - shuffle out of them, because they were married. Well I don't thi
nk that's fair. If you take a job - mind - my idea you've got to have superhuman strength to - run a house, keep up with a man's - fancies, and - what else shall I say - yes, and do the job. Without sacrificing one or the other. And I think they ought to 
b
e satisfied with either - being married, or not being married. They ought to make that decision early in life. But having made it - either - you must put somebody in your house to run it for you. And not interfere, but I don't think that you - ought to ex
pect the single girl - to do your job for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. There was no talk of anything else was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you go up and down each day to Cardiff University?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You didn't live in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh no. Didn't live in Aberdare Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh dear no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 With your adopted brother or sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, no. We just went on - from there as if it hadn't happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No. I never thought of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You had to go did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - I did except - when the strike was on. Do you remember when - there was a strike on, and the men were asking for more - m
oney and - we had to go and feed the children. I used to walk up from Pontypridd to Havard then. Every Sunday morning. To see the children, give them their breakfast. And there were no buses running you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 That would be the general strike after the war would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
What about before the end of the first world war when you left school and went to Cardiff University, did you spend your Sunday any differently then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh dear no. My mother was a very strict Sabbat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8280004\charrsid8088101 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 rian. And she was 
head of the house. She didn't like you to - pour a cup of tea for her. She was the head of the house, and she didn't like you to pour a cup of tea for her, and she didn't like you to find her place in church. She kept the head of the house 'til the end. A
nd we accepted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well we accepted it. Well it was - mother's house and that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 So you would go to church morning and night, and Sunday school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No,
 not very much. Particular if I knew people, but not otherwise. I liked Arthur Pearson. I - although he was thought by - we used to have a - what they called a Mutual Improvement Society, in - St. David's, and of course that meant that - we used to argue 
about different things. And very often - he and I were not on the same side. But although we weren't on the same side like that we were still sort of friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Was he the M.P. then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 He was - no, he was a - on the Council then. Any difference - to our relationships. With one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No, not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What were your views then in politics, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well I think I was a snob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What political views would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I was never Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Why were your views like that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Well I don't know. Of course my father was very much - against people having things for nothing. And he believed that if you won a scholarship - and you could afford to pay for it, it wa
s your place to pay for it and leave that scholarship to the next poor person to have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 This period up to 1913 in Pontypridd must have been a very interesting time because that's when things were changing wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. Yes. And of course 
- there was a strong religious element wasn't there. And you could tell the time - on Sunday - by the people going to church and coming home from church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would everybody go in Pontypridd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well - not everybody, but - very many. The majority, put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you vote in the general election before 1919, 1919 was the first for women wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Of course my mother was a suffragette.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you remember voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You don't remember what part you voted for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh the Liberals. We were strong Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 You were saying that you had this Mutual Improvement Society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How would you spend your spare time, was there anything else like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 There was the - this was - yes - well, I think we used to go to the prayer meeting and the - you know, the - church meetings. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 When you were in college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. My mother saw we went there. She was a very strong character. And she ruled the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Did you do any different things, those were the same things as you were doing before weren't they? Did you do anything different when you went to college or when you started work at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I - I used to - do a - a lot of hand work. Crocheting and - handwork of - embroidery and - I used to go to - evening classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Millinery classes and - what you call - and needlework classes. And of course - First Aid and home nursing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Who would you go with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 I went a lot of times with my sister. Then sometimes - it would be the people next door, the Jones and those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 The minister and Philip Jones' daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Oh yes. I had a - few friends in Abergavenny - boyfriends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 How did you meet them, the new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 By going over there to stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you have any new friends in your own area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes, as new - new people came - into the area you got to know them, and you became friendly with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 What about when you went to Cardiff University, would you make any new friends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes. You met people from other areas, like Barry and Merthyr and - places like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you have any special friends at this time? Boys or girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, I had a - special friend in Abergavenny. Boyfriend. Used to take me out quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Where would you go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh we'd - got to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Hereford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or
 to - places like that. We did a good deal of cycling. Cycling - the - cars were off the roads weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 There were very few in those days weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. Because that - that's where I learnt to cycle, in Gower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 The Coastguards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Would you do anything else, any special girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes, I - I had one especial friend - that came from Merthyr and married and came from Merthyr, I was very friendly with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your mother that would be, your father was dead by this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did she expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did you have to be home by - a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes. It wasn't the question - 'cos if we were only going to 
chapel - she'd expect us back at nine o'clock. But if we were going - to see a friend - we'd - come back later. But she liked to know where we were and she didn't like us out after dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Your mother died early in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Did things change at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
Not appreciably I don't think. Only at - of course shops and things - were a bit difficult because - shopping was difficult wasn't it then. And you couldn't get things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Because the war was still on?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\tx5727\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid861 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405022\charrsid8088101 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid861 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 But life didn'
t change much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Well I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Oh I don't know. Oh well that was about it I expect,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Thirty-seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824748 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4873271\charrsid8088101 Yes.
\par }}